artbynyannahtmlquestionsandanswers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">how to center text on a border background</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Please tell me what html I use to center text on a border background. <BR> Thanks</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=000066><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://server2.ezboard.com:8080/unyanna.showPublicProfile>nyanna</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.nyanna.com/art/nstar.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#9966ff>8/13/99</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#9966ff>1:09:01 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fartbynyannahtmlquestionsandanswers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=1><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: how to center text on a border background</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">The best way to handle border backgrounds is to use tables and make your first table cell the width of your border.   <BR>   <BR> For example, if your border is 140 pixels wide you should code something like this:   <BR>   <BR> >table width=&quot;100%&quot;<   <BR> >tr<   <BR> >td width=140<   <BR> >/td<   <BR>   <BR> >td width=500<   <BR> >center<   <BR>   <BR> ...PUT YOUR CONTENT HERE...   <BR>   <BR> >/center<   <BR> >/td<   <BR> >/tr<   <BR> >/table<   <BR>   <BR>   <BR> Of course you must reverse the angle brackets.   <BR>   <BR> As a side note, I try to keep the total width within the table at 640 or less if possible because many people will be viewing with a 640 x 480 resolution.</font><P>      -<a href="http://www.nyanna.com/art" target="_blank">nyanna</a><br><a href="http://www.nyanna.com/art" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.nyanna.com/art/018.gif" border=0></a><P><i><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Edited by <A HREF=http://server2.ezboard.com:8080/unyanna.showPublicProfile>nyanna</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.nyanna.com/art/nstar.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10> at: 8/14/99 1:05:44 pm</FONT><br></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=000033><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://server2.ezboard.com:8080/ukyoddie.showPublicProfile>kyoddie</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#9966ff>8/13/99</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#9966ff>11:04:50 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fartbynyannahtmlquestionsandanswers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=2><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: how to center text on a border background</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Thanks very much for the quick reply. I did it and now all my text is centered. What I realy ment was, how can I keep the text off of the border. I want it to be on the left side but not right in the center. I thought there was something what you put on right after your background with a % in it.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=000066><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://server2.ezboard.com:8080/unyanna.showPublicProfile>nyanna</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.nyanna.com/art/nstar.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#9966ff>8/14/99</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#9966ff>8:39:46 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT>